Package: antispam
Version: 0.11
Revision: 1
###
Depends: db3-shlibs, logrotate, daemonic
BuildDepends: db3
###
Source: http://alf.di.fct.unl.pt/AntiSpam/download//%n-%v.tgz
Source-MD5: 4e639a321e4bfbe30aa1506e5e82e6c2
###
PatchScript: sed -e 's,@FINKINSTALL@,%i,g' -e 's,@FINKPREFIX@,%p,g' %a/%f.patch | patch -p1
###
ConfFiles: %p/etc/antispam.cfg
###
CompileScript: make
###
DaemonicName: antispam
DaemonicFile: <<
  <service>
    <description>Antispam Mail Relay authentication</description>
    <message>Antispam Mail Relay authentication</message>

    <daemon name="antispam">
      <executable background="yes">%p/sbin/antispam</executable>
      <!-- the daemon will background itself, but may take a while
           to start up to the point where it does so -->
      <pidfile>%p/var/run/antispam.pid</pidfile>
    </daemon>

  </service>
<<
###
Description: Mail Relay authentication via POP-3
DescDetail: <<
  AntiSpam is a daemon that keeps an eye on the mail log and watches for POP3
  logins on the machine. For each successful POP3 login antispam keeps a
  record of the originating machine's IP and allows it to use the local
  mail relay. It's totally easy to configure.
<<
